📘 Project Lifecycle (End-to-End Flow)

🔹 1. Project Lifecycle
Sales

Client acquisition and deal closure
(Client ko onboard karta hai aur deal close karta hai)

Pre-Sales

Requirement gathering and analysis
(Client ko kya chahiye?)

TPM (Technical Project Manager)

Project planning, execution and coordination
(Project ka timeline, planning aur coordination handle karta hai)

Enterprise Architect

Overall system design and technology decision
(Pura system ka architecture design karta hai aur technology decide karta hai)

🔹 2. Architecture Roles
Infra Architect

Designs infrastructure, networking and cloud setup
(Network, cloud, servers aur security design karta hai)

Application Architect

Designs application structure and backend logic
(App ka structure, APIs aur backend logic design karta hai)

🔹 3. 3-Tier Architecture
Frontend

Handles user interface and client interaction
(User ko jo dikhta hai — UI, buttons, pages)

Backend

Handles business logic and processing
(Data process karta hai aur frontend ko response deta hai)

Database

Stores and manages application data
(Data ko store karta hai aur retrieve karta hai)

🔹 4. HLD vs LLD
High Level Design (HLD)

Defines overall architecture and system flow
(Big picture — cloud/on-prem, components, architecture flow)

Low Level Design (LLD)

Defines detailed implementation and configuration
(Exact IPs, ports, configs aur DB schema define hota hai)

🔹 5. Deployment Models
On-Premise

Infrastructure hosted in own data center
(Apna server aur data center hota hai)

Cloud

Infrastructure hosted on cloud platforms
(Azure, AWS, GCP par deploy hota hai)

