Subnet

Divides network into smaller parts
(Network ko chhote parts me todta hai)

Virtual Network (VNet)

Private isolated network in cloud
(Cloud ke andar private network hota hai)

Route Table

Controls traffic routing path
(Traffic kahan jayega define karta hai)

🔹 7. Ghar / Building Analogy
Network as building

Entire system behaves like a building
(Pura network ek building jaisa hota hai)

Subnet as floors

Each subnet is a separate floor
(Har subnet ek floor hota hai)

IP as rooms

Each device has a unique room
(Har device ek room jaisa hota hai)

Gateway as main gate

Entry and exit point
(Building ka gate hota hai)

Firewall as security guard

Controls access to building
(Security guard decide karta hai kaun andar aayega)

Load balancer as lift

Distributes users across floors
(Lift logon ko alag floors me bhejta hai)

Application gateway as reception

Routes users to correct destination
(Reception user ko sahi jagah bhejta hai)

NAT as exit permission

Allows internal users to access outside
(Bahar jane ke liye permission deta hai)

DNS as directory

Maps names to locations
(Building directory jaisa kaam karta hai)

Router as CCTV

Monitors all network activity
(Router sab activity dekh raha hota hai)

Reserved IPs as special rooms

Used only by system
(System ke liye reserved hote hain)

🔹 8. Traffic Flow
Full request flow

User request travels through system layers
(Request system ke multiple layers se pass hoti hai)

User → DNS → Gateway → Load Balancer → Backend → Database

🔹 9. Router Monitoring
Router observes traffic

Tracks IPs, domains and data flow
(Router dekh sakta hai kaun kya access kar raha hai)

HTTPS encrypts data

Content cannot be read fully
(Actual data hidden hota hai)

DNS reveals domains

Visited websites can be identified
(Kaunsi site open hui pata chal jata hai)

Public WiFi risk

Network owner can monitor activity
(Public WiFi me tracking possible hoti hai)

🔹 10. Security
Firewall

Filters traffic based on rules
(Traffic allow ya block karta hai)

NSG

Controls inbound and outbound traffic
(Network rules define karta hai)

🔹 11. NAT
NAT converts private IP to public IP

Enables internet access
(Private system internet access kar sakta hai)

🔹 12. Load Balancer
Distributes traffic

Prevents overload and improves performance
(Server load manage karta hai)

🔹 13. Application Gateway
Smart routing

Routes traffic based on URL and protocol
(Intelligent routing karta hai)

🔹 14. Ports
Ports identify services

Each service runs on a specific port
(Har service ka port hota hai)

Examples:
80 → HTTP
443 → HTTPS
22 → SSH

🔹 15. Scaling
Vertical scaling

Increase server power
(Server strong banate hain)

Horizontal scaling

Increase number of servers
(Server count badhate hain)

🔹 16. Availability
High availability

System stays running during failure
(System chalta rehta hai)

Fault tolerance

System auto-recovers
(System automatically handle karta hai)

🔹 17. Region & Zone
Region

Geographical location of data center
(Location hota hai)

Availability Zone

Multiple isolated locations
(Safe zones hote hain)
